file: README.md
behavior: Top-level orientation document for an MVP scaffolding repo implementing an opinionated agentic coding system; points readers to the sealed spec, the unimplemented-work list, and the repo layout.
edit_notes:
  - Must stay in sync with docs/SPEC.md (full spec) and docs/UNIMPLEMENTED.md (TODO list); this file only summarizes/links them.
  - References a sibling repo at ../meal-planning/ (CLI meal planner) as the reference consumer, kept outside this repo intentionally for sandbox isolation.
  - Quickstart steps describe a workflow (ctx-access init-task/end-task, .context/ tree, summarizer prompts) that is not yet implemented ("once implemented").
